2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The concept of codewords is related to information theory, and the paper discusses the existence/nonexistence of certain types of codewords. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper uses techniques from symbolic computation and satisfiability checking, which are related to computational complexity. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The use of satisfiability checking and the creation of a certificate of unsatisfiability are related to logic in computer science. 
5. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) - The paper uses techniques from symbolic computation to verify the nonexistence of projective planes of order ten with weight 15 codewords.
